life is like a sandwich. no matter which way you flip it, the bread always comes up first.\n the best advice my teacher ever told me is: keep your eyes on your own paper.

My mentor Ryaan Ahmed gave me some beneficial advice on knowing what to spend your time on. If you're deciding between going into big tech, startup, nonprofit, retail, school, etc. you need a framework for this decision. The framework Ryaan showed me is finding something that gives you the lifestyle, impact, and education you want. I want to work on a startup to have a lifestyle that allows me to meet new people and think of complex problems all the time so that I can push the world in new directions. I want to work on a startup to impact underserved communities and improve the lives of everyone. I want to be in a startup to learn something new every day and get out of my comfort zone to code something new, network with someone new, or understand some new legal procedure. For these reasons, I want to pursue making a startup. Use this framework to decide where you are and where you will be.
